snippet: The number of people who signed up for private health insurance under the Affordable Care Act in February declined for the second month in a row.
abstract: Federal officials say almost one million people signed up in February 2014 for private health insurance under Affordable Care Act, bringing the total to date to 4.2 million but leaving Obama administration well short of its original target set by Department of Health and Human Services, with less than month to go before end of open enrollment period.
lead_paragraph: The number of people who signed up for private health insurance under the Affordable Care Act in February declined for the second month in a row.
